race.comment: STRAAND CARE (3) returned from a lengthy spell with a tenacious on-pace second over 1200m at Scone with the 61kg. Lone win came second-up and will appreciate the drop back to 1000m. Expecting him to go on with it this time in. LORD OF THE SUN (4) consistent gelding racing in a rich vein of form. Stalked the speed first-up when he closed off strongly for a narrow second over 1100m at Armidale. Comes to hand quickly and can figure prominently. SOLAR BLAST (5) resumes for the new yard after doing the bulk of his racing in South Australia. Total forgive from the sticky draw when twelfth over 1200m at Morphettville in BM68 grade. Lugging bit goes on and must be kept safe. SINGING STAR (2) underrated mare resuming. Will relish the class drop and she has a good record over this track and trip. Looks ready to go after the slick trial win over 800m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Gets every chance from the barrier.
